Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Andersonin-Y1 (UCLL1; natural AMPs; frog, amphibians, animals)

Literature Information.Literature: It contains one additional N-terminal Ile compared to AP1823.Activity: Active against Gram- bacteria E. coli (MIC 3.2 ug/ml), B. pyocyaneus (now called P. aeruginosa) (MIC 3.2 ug/ml), Gram+ bacteria S. aureus (MIC 1.6 ug/ml), and yeast C. albicans (MIC 1.6 ug/ml).You can rotate, zoom, and view the structureherein the PDB. LA turn is lcoated 5-9 and a short helix is annotated for residues 13-16 (Pal et al. 2019). Updated 4/2019; 3/2020, 7/2021
